alaIND1Dot1XMIBGroups.name: alaIND1Dot1XMIBGroups
alaIND1Dot1XMIBGroups.description: Branch For 802.1X Subsystem Units Of Conformance.

ALADot1xClassificationPolicyType.name: ALADot1xClassificationPolicyType
ALADot1xClassificationPolicyType.description: This policy type is the classification policy used to classify a device onto the system.

ALADot1xAuthenticationResult.name: ALADot1xAuthenticationResult
ALADot1xAuthenticationResult.description: The result of the authentication. If the ALADot1xAuthenticationType of this device is noAuthentication then this object will return notApplicable. If the authentication has not completed then this object will return inProgress.

ALADot1xMacLearntState.name: ALADot1xMacLearntState
ALADot1xMacLearntState.description: The state of MAC address in the system

ALADot1xMacQueryType.name: ALADot1xMacQueryType
ALADot1xMacQueryType.description: The query type of MAC address in the system. This query MAC address type is used to specify which type of MAC address to query from the alaDot1xDeviceStatusTable.

ALADot1xDeviceType.name: ALADot1xDeviceType
ALADot1xDeviceType.description: The type of device. Either supplicant or non-supplicant.

alaDot1xPortTable.name: alaDot1xPortTable
alaDot1xPortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

alaDot1xPortSlotNumber.name: alaDot1xPortSlotNumber
alaDot1xPortSlotNumber.description: The slot that the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber resides.

alaDot1xPortPortNumber.name: alaDot1xPortPortNumber
alaDot1xPortPortNumber.description: The user port that the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber resides.

alaDot1xPortMACAddress.name: alaDot1xPortMACAddress
alaDot1xPortMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the supplicant that along with the slot and port uniquely form the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber.

alaDot1xPortVlan.name: alaDot1xPortVlan
alaDot1xPortVlan.description: The vlan that the supplicant is authorized to access.

alaDot1xPortProtocol.name: alaDot1xPortProtocol
alaDot1xPortProtocol.description: The protocol that is authorized for the supplicant. This is used in conjunction with the alaDot1xPortVlan object. Supplicant can be authorized to different vlans for different protocol.

alaDot1xPortUserName.name: alaDot1xPortUserName
alaDot1xPortUserName.description: The user name of the supplicant used for authentication.

alaDot1xSupplicantPolicyUsed.name: alaDot1xSupplicantPolicyUsed
alaDot1xSupplicantPolicyUsed.description: Classification Policy under which the 802.1x supplicant is learned.

alaDot1xMacTable.name: alaDot1xMacTable
alaDot1xMacTable.description: Provide the list of users currently authenticated into the switch for bridging purpose.

alaDot1xMACAddress.name: alaDot1xMACAddress
alaDot1xMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the supplicant that along with the slot and port uniquely form the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber.

alaDot1xMacIfIndex.name: alaDot1xMacIfIndex
alaDot1xMacIfIndex.description: Interface index in which alaDot1xMACAddress was learned.

alaDot1xMacSlotNumber.name: alaDot1xMacSlotNumber
alaDot1xMacSlotNumber.description: The slot in which alaDot1xMACAddress was learned.

alaDot1xMacPortNumber.name: alaDot1xMacPortNumber
alaDot1xMacPortNumber.description: The user port in which alaDot1xMACAddress was learned.

alaDot1xMacVlan.name: alaDot1xMacVlan
alaDot1xMacVlan.description: The vlan that the supplicant is authorized to access.

alaDot1xMacProtocol.name: alaDot1xMacProtocol
alaDot1xMacProtocol.description: The protocol that is authorized for the supplicant. This is used in conjunction with the alaDot1xMacVlan object. Supplicant can be authorized to different vlans for different protocol.

alaDot1xMacUserName.name: alaDot1xMacUserName
alaDot1xMacUserName.description: The user name of the supplicant used for authentication.

alaDot1xMacState.name: alaDot1xMacState
alaDot1xMacState.description: The State of the port in which the current mac-address was learned.

alaDot1xMacSupplicantPolicyUsed.name: alaDot1xMacSupplicantPolicyUsed
alaDot1xMacSupplicantPolicyUsed.description: Classification Policy under which the 802.1x supplicant is learned.

alaDot1xPortLookupTable.name: alaDot1xPortLookupTable
alaDot1xPortLookupTable.description: A table of which allows to find the logical port number given the physical slot/port/MAC. An entry appears in this table for each logical port of this system.

alaDot1xPortLookupEntry.name: alaDot1xPortLookupEntry
alaDot1xPortLookupEntry.description: The translation table to look up the dot1xPaePortNumber.

alaDot1xPortLookupSlotNumber.name: alaDot1xPortLookupSlotNumber
alaDot1xPortLookupSlotNumber.description: The slot that the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber resides.

alaDot1xPortLookupPortNumber.name: alaDot1xPortLookupPortNumber
alaDot1xPortLookupPortNumber.description: The physical port that the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber resides.

alaDot1xPortLookupMACAddress.name: alaDot1xPortLookupMACAddress
alaDot1xPortLookupMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the supplicant that along with the slot and port uniquely form the logical port represented by the dot1xPaePortNumber.

alaDot1xPortLookupInterfaceNumber.name: alaDot1xPortLookupInterfaceNumber
alaDot1xPortLookupInterfaceNumber.description: The ifIndex that represnets the slot and port where the dot1xPaePortNumber resides.

alaDot1xNonSupplicantTable.name: alaDot1xNonSupplicantTable
alaDot1xNonSupplicantTable.description: A table of non 802.1x supplicants learned on 802.1x authenticated ports.

alaDot1xNonSupplicantIntfNum.name: alaDot1xNonSupplicantIntfNum
alaDot1xNonSupplicantIntfNum.description: The ifIndex represneting the slot and port where the non 802.1x supplicant is learned.

alaDot1xNonSupplicantMACAddress.name: alaDot1xNonSupplicantMACAddress
alaDot1xNonSupplicantMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the non 802.1x supplicant.

alaDot1xNonSupplicantVlanID.name: alaDot1xNonSupplicantVlanID
alaDot1xNonSupplicantVlanID.description: The Id of the VLAN on which the non 802.1x supplicant is learned.

alaDot1xNonSupplicantPolicyUsed.name: alaDot1xNonSupplicantPolicyUsed
alaDot1xNonSupplicantPolicyUsed.description: Classification policy under which the non 802.1x supplicant is learned.

alaDot1xAuthenticationStatus.name: alaDot1xAuthenticationStatus
alaDot1xAuthenticationStatus.description: Authentication status of the non 802.1x supplicant.

alaDot1xAuthPolicyTable.name: alaDot1xAuthPolicyTable
alaDot1xAuthPolicyTable.description: A table of supplicant and non supplicant device classification policies as they are configured on 802.1x authenticated ports.

alaDot1xAuthPolicyIntfNumber.name: alaDot1xAuthPolicyIntfNumber
alaDot1xAuthPolicyIntfNumber.description: The ifIndex that represnets the slot and port where the device classification policies are configured.

alaDot1xNonSuppPolicy.name: alaDot1xNonSuppPolicy
alaDot1xNonSuppPolicy.description: MAC based authentication -> M Group Mobility -> G VLAN ID -> <vlan id> Default VLAN -> D Block -> B Fail -> , Captive Portal -> C Examples: MGD,GB. The default value is B (block). If the string size is zero (0), the default value is used.

alaDot1xSuppPolicy.name: alaDot1xSuppPolicy
alaDot1xSuppPolicy.description: 802.1x authentication -> X Group Mobility -> G VLAN ID -> <vlan id> Default VLAN -> D Block -> B Fail -> , Captive Portal -> C Default value: XGD,B. If the string size is zero (0), the default value is used.

alaDot1xPollingCnt.name: alaDot1xPollingCnt
alaDot1xPollingCnt.description: Number of retries to poll the end station for EAPoL frame before classifying the end station with group mobility or guest vlan ID configured. If the value is set to zero (0), it indicates a special case where the port will ignore any EAP frame from the client and this will force all devices to the non-supplicant policy for classification.

alaDot1xCaptivePortalPolicy.name: alaDot1xCaptivePortalPolicy
alaDot1xCaptivePortalPolicy.description: Web authentication -> W Group Mobility -> G VLAN ID -> <vlan id> Default VLAN -> D Block -> B Fail -> , Default value: XGD,B, if string size is zero, the default value is used.

alaDot1xCPortalSessionLimit.name: alaDot1xCPortalSessionLimit
alaDot1xCPortalSessionLimit.description: Captive Portal Session limit is the interval that a Captive Portal user can login. User is to be logged off after the session limit. If the session limit is set to zero (0), it means the session is unlimited, user will not be automatically logged off.

alaDot1xCPortalRetryCnt.name: alaDot1xCPortalRetryCnt
alaDot1xCPortalRetryCnt.description: Number of retries for the Captive Portal user to provide the user credential before the software will classify the user to the failed policy according the the alaDot1xCaptivePortalPolicy.

alaDot1xCPortalIpAddress.name: alaDot1xCPortalIpAddress
alaDot1xCPortalIpAddress.description: The factory default Captive Portal IP address is 10.123.0.1. If the 10.123.0.0 subnet is already in use, user can change the Captive Portal IP address to another 10.x.0.0 subnet. Only the second octet of the Captive Portal IP address can be changed.

alaDot1xCPortalProxyURL.name: alaDot1xCPortalProxyURL
alaDot1xCPortalProxyURL.description: The factory default for Captive Portal working with proxy server url has the key word proxy. If the user's proxy server url does not have the key work proxy, user can use this object to specify the proxy server url. If none is specified this object will return the default value - proxy.

alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthSuccessRedirectUR.name: alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthSuccessRedirectURL
alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthSuccessRedirectUR.description: Captive Portal's Redirect URL upon successful authentication.

alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthFailRedirectURL.name: alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthFailRedirectURL
alaDot1xCPortalPostAuthFailRedirectURL.description: Captive Portal's Redirect URL upon failed authentication.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusTable.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusTable
alaDot1xDeviceStatusTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusEntry.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusEntry
alaDot1xDeviceStatusEntry.description: One entry of the Device Status Table.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacQueryType.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacQueryType
alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacQueryType.description: The type of MAC address to query.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusSlotNumber.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusSlotNumber
alaDot1xDeviceStatusSlotNumber.description: The slot that the device reporting the status resides.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusPortNumber.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusPortNumber
alaDot1xDeviceStatusPortNumber.description: The user port that the device reporting the status resides.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusMACAddress.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusMACAddress
alaDot1xDeviceStatusMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the device reporting the status.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusDeviceType.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusDeviceType
alaDot1xDeviceStatusDeviceType.description: The type of device. Either supplicant or non-supplicant.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusVlan.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusVlan
alaDot1xDeviceStatusVlan.description: The vlan that the device reporting the status is authorized to access.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusIPAddress.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusIPAddress
alaDot1xDeviceStatusIPAddress.description: The IP address of the device reporting the status.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusUserName.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusUserName
alaDot1xDeviceStatusUserName.description: The user name of the device reporting the status.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusProfileUsed.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusProfileUsed
alaDot1xDeviceStatusProfileUsed.description: The name of the User Network Profile entry used when the device reporting the status is classified.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusAuthType.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusAuthType
alaDot1xDeviceStatusAuthType.description: The type of authentication used by the device reporting the status to obtain network access.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusPolicyUsed.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusPolicyUsed
alaDot1xDeviceStatusPolicyUsed.description: Classification Policy under which the device is learned.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacLearntState.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacLearntState
alaDot1xDeviceStatusMacLearntState.description: The State of the MAC classified in the switch.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusTimeLearned.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusTimeLearned
alaDot1xDeviceStatusTimeLearned.description: The time that the MAC address is learned in the system.

alaDot1xDeviceStatusCaptivePortalUsed.name: alaDot1xDeviceStatusCaptivePortalUsed
alaDot1xDeviceStatusCaptivePortalUsed.description: The object indicates if the device is classified in the system using Captive Portal. A value of True means that the device has used Captive Portal to authenticate its credential and a value of False means that the device has not used Captive Portal to authenticate its credential.

alaDot1xAdminLogoutType.name: alaDot1xAdminLogoutType
alaDot1xAdminLogoutType.description: When this variable is set, the switch is to logout the user based on the logout type. The associated MIB object should be correctly set based on the logout type. If the corresponding MIB object that contain the criteria is not set correctly the switch will not be able to perform the logout operation. After the logout operation is done, the switch will set the corresponding criteria to back to its default value. Also when the logout operation is done, the switch is to set this variable back to zero (0).

alaDot1xAdminLogoutMacAddress.name: alaDot1xAdminLogoutMacAddress
alaDot1xAdminLogoutMacAddress.description: This value is used only if alaDot1xAdminLogoutType is set to MAC address. The default value is set to ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff. This well know broadcast MAC address will not be learned by the switch. The switch will reset this to the default value after the logout operation is performed

alaDot1xAdminLogoutUserName.name: alaDot1xAdminLogoutUserName
alaDot1xAdminLogoutUserName.description: This value is used only if alaDot1xAdminLogoutType is set to username. The default is a NULL string. The switch will reset this to the default value after the logout operation is performed. User is not allowed to set the value to NULL.

alaDot1xAdminLogoutNetworkProfileName.name: alaDot1xAdminLogoutNetworkProfileName
alaDot1xAdminLogoutNetworkProfileName.description: This value is used only if alaDot1xAdminLogoutType is set to networkprofilename. The default is a NULL string. The switch will reset this to the default value after the logout operation is performed. User is not allowed to set the value to NULL.

alaDot1xAdminLogoutInterfaceId.name: alaDot1xAdminLogoutInterfaceId
alaDot1xAdminLogoutInterfaceId.description: This value is used only if alaDot1xAdminLogoutType is set to interfaceId. The default value is zero (0). The switch will reset this to the default value after the logout operation is performed.

alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutPolicy.name: alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutPolicy
alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutPolicy.description: Block -> B User Network Profile -> 'user network profile name' Default value is B.

alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutReAuthPeriod.name: alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutReAuthPeriod
alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutReAuthPeriod.description: This is the time interval in second that the supplicant is to be classified according to the Auth Server Down Policy (alaDot1xAuthServerTimeoutPolicy). When this time is expired, the supplicant will be prompted to re-authenticate and see if the Auth Server is back up. The default value is 30 seconds.

alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutStatus.name: alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutStatus
alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutStatus.description: This is object is to enable or disable the use of alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutPolicy and alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutReAuthPeriod. Default is disabled.

alaDot1xPassthroughStatus.name: alaDot1xPassthroughStatus
alaDot1xPassthroughStatus.description: Passthrough of 802.1x packets. Force the 802.1x packet to flood in the VLAN.

alaAvlanPassthroughStatus.name: alaAvlanPassthroughStatus
alaAvlanPassthroughStatus.description: Passthrough of AVLAN packets. Force the AVLAN packet to flood in the VLAN.

alaINDDot1XPortGroup.name: alaINDDot1XPortGroup
alaINDDot1XPortGroup.description: Collection of 802.1x objects for port status.

alaDot1xPortLookupGroup.name: alaDot1xPortLookupGroup
alaDot1xPortLookupGroup.description: Collection of 802.1x objects for port lookup.

alaINDDot1XPolicyGroup.name: alaINDDot1XPolicyGroup
alaINDDot1XPolicyGroup.description: Collection of 802.1x objects for supplicant and non-supplicant policies.

alaINDDot1XDeviceStatusGroup.name: alaINDDot1XDeviceStatusGroup
alaINDDot1XDeviceStatusGroup.description: Collection of 802.1x objects for the status of the devices on an 802.1X enable port.

alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutGroup.name: alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutGroup
alaDot1xAuthSvrTimeoutGroup.description: Collection of 802.1x objects for the Authentication Server Timeout.

alaPassthroughConfigGroup.name: alaPassthroughConfigGroup
alaPassthroughConfigGroup.description: Status of passthrough for 802.1x and avlan configuration in devices.
